[[File:PhilHardingArchaeologist.jpg|thumb|John Gater (left) with archaeologist [[Phil Harding (archaeologist)|Phil Harding]] at a ''[[Time Team]]'' shoot in 2007]]
'''John Gater''' is a British [[Archaeological geophysics|archaeological geophysicist]], who has regularly featured on ''[[Time Team]]'' &ndash; the [[Channel 4]] [[archaeological]] television series &ndash; since 1993.

He was educated at the [[University of Bradford]] and graduated with a [[BSc]] Archaeological Sciences in 1979. He worked with [[British Gas plc|British Gas]] (for five years), the Ancient Monuments Laboratory ([[English Heritage]]) and Bradford University Research.

In 1986 he set up Geophysical Surveys of Bradford (GSB), an independent consultancy in geophysics for archaeology. In 1983 he became a member of the [[Institute of Field Archaeologists]] and is now also an [[associate editor]] for the ''Journal of Archaeological Prospection''.

On 21 July 2006, Gater was awarded an [[Honorary degree|honorary]] [[Doctor of Science]] by the University of Bradford for his "distinguished contributions to the field of Archaeological Geophysics".<ref>[https://archive.is/20070610012338/http://www.brad.ac.uk/acad/archsci/depart/gaffney_gater.php Honorary Doctorates for Chris Gaffney and John Gater<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

On the DVD set ''The Very Best Time Team Digs'', John states that, as of the time of the DVD's production, his favourite dig was [[Turkdean]] (the only site where the quality of the archaeological data was so good that ''Time Team'' returned at a later date to dig it again).

