'''Solar weather''' is branch of [[meteorology]], which studies the behavior of the sun and how those behaviors can be predicted.<ref>Arnold Hanslmeier (2007). ''The Sun and Space Weather'' (2nd Edition).  Springer; Softcover reprint of hardcover 2nd ed. 2007 edition. {{ISBN|978-9048174065}}</ref>
Solar weather research involves developing and running simulations of solar behavior, as well as observing the sun using observation equipment.

Due to the enormous size and mass of the sun, solar weather predictions aren’t as precise as earth-weather predictions. 

Solar weather is closely related to  [[space weather]] and often included in same category.

